In addition to these dreams, he felt an urge to meet this woman. Somehow, he was drawn towards her. He continued to dream of her and the things she did, nearly as if they were his own memories.<br>
<br>
After a long journey, all across the world of Norrath, they finally met. Kamasu found out that Nadera had dreamed of him just like he had dreamed of her, and that she, also, had felt an urge to meet him. They showed each other their rings, and somehow knew they had to touch them together.<br>
A searing light blinded the two for a moment, then, after it subsided, a spirit emerged from the two rings.<br>
The spirit said to them, in a deep, resounding voice: &quot;I am Ulasthar, Guardian of the Realm of Immortal Souls. I can guide you to a place where souls who prove themselves worthy can live forever in joy and happiness. Kamasu and Nadera, you will henceforth be called Keepers of the Rings. You may access the Realm of Immortal Souls and your duty it shall be to find more like-minded people who prove themselves worthy. By the power of the Rings, you can make them Trusted Souls who can access the Realm of Immortal Souls, just like you can, as long as they adhere to my Commandments.&quot;<br>
He then told them of his Commandments, the rules Trusted Souls have to adhere to to be able to access the Realm of Immortal Souls.<br>
<br>
In addition to that, Ulasthar gave a quest. &quot;Seek out the dark elf called Grevenil. Even though his skin is black, his heart is golden deep inside. Once you find him, bring him to me, when needed i will explain later. I will call upon Namyra, a capable tracker, to aid you in your search for Grevenil..... Make haste.&quot;<br>
Grevenil proved more elusive than Kamasu and Nadera had imagined, but after a long search, aided by the human ranger Namyra, they finally found Grevenil. They became close friends, despite their differences, altho dark elves generally are known for their vileness, both Grevenil and Namyra proved to be reliable and trustworthy allies to the Keepers. When they returned to Ulasthar, they learned about Grevenil as a capable scout and clever tactician, Ulasthar gave Grevenil the task to be the Protector of the Ring, to protect the Keepers and train all other Trusted Souls in the arts of war so they can protect themselves and those they love from those who would wish them ill. Ulasthar made Namyra his Loremaster, entrusted with keeping secrets and teaching them to those who are worthy. He also told the Keepers that this was the last quest he had had for them and disappeared, the words &quot;Friendship is a powerful weapon!&quot; echoing inside their minds.<br>
Many joined their cause, and many more shall follow their path for centuries to come.<br>
this was the story of Kamasu, Nadera, and the Realm of Immortal Souls. Where I learnt the story? Well, my name... is Kamasu.  <p><center><p>
